The article reports that President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued an Executive Order declaring a national emergency due to the threat posed by harmful foreign activities of the Russian government. The specified activities include attempts to undermine democratic elections and institutions, engage in malicious cyber activities, use corruption to influence foreign governments, target dissidents or journalists, undermine security in countries important to US national security, and violate international law. The President has determined that these activities constitute an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. The article includes a copy of the Executive Order. The report is addressed to the Congress of the United States and was issued on April 15, 2021, from the White House.